{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "18", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "18", "M": "31", "S": "03"}}, "news": [{"title": "Nashik civic body to launch drive to check rainwater harvesting systems", "para": "The Nashik Municipal Corporation is launching an inspection drive to ensure rainwater harvesting systems are functional in buildings of 500sqm or more. Mayor Himgauri Aher instructed officials to review existing systems and consider penalties for non-compliance. Incentives for reporting violations and voluntary installations are also being explored to improve groundwater levels.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/nashik-municipal-corporation-to-ramp-up-inspection-of-rainwater-harvesting-systems/130351576?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-51190/130351576.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Lucknow development body launches OTS for around 4,000 defaulters", "para": "The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is launching a One-Time Settlement (OTS) program to aid approximately 4,000 defaulters. This initiative offers relief from penalties and compound interest, allowing allottees to regularize ownership by clearing dues. Applications will be processed within three months, with a 3% rebate for full payments made within 30 days.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/lucknow-development-authority-introduces-one-time-settlement-plan-for-4000-defaulting-property-owners/130351522?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-65720/130351522.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Surat: Pragya Nagar won\u2019t be charged property tax", "para": "Surat Municipal Corporation has waived property tax for residents of Pragya Nagar after their homes were demolished in 2025. The civic body took this step after residents received tax bills for the upcoming year, despite their colony no longer existing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/surat-residents-of-pragya-nagar-exempt-from-property-tax-following-demolition/130351468?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96144/130351468.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}